    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/vr-02-experimental-hemolysis-benchmark",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Experimental benchmark — relative hemolysis index comparison against FDA pump in vitro data across all five flow-speed operating points",
      "comparedAgainst": "https://uofa.net/morrison/data/fda-pump-experimental-hemolysis",
      "description": "The CFD model was exercised at five operating conditions (3 L/min at 2500 RPM, 3 L/min at 3500 RPM, 4.5 L/min at 2500 RPM, 4.5 L/min at 3500 RPM, and 6 L/min at 3000 RPM) representative of the clinical CPB envelope. Predicted relative hemolysis index (RH) values were computed using the power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen et al.) integrated along Lagrangian particle trajectories seeded uniformly at the pump inlet. RH predictions ranged from 0.61 to 0.89 across the five operating points, all satisfying the RH < 1.0 acceptance criterion. Comparison against the in vitro hemolysis measurements from the FDA generic centrifugal pump test report showed mean absolute error of 0.07 RH units (8.4% of the acceptance threshold), well within the ±15% validation tolerance established in the validation plan. Spatial convergence was confirmed at GCI < 2.3% for the worst-case operating point. Turbulence model sensitivity was assessed by comparing k-ω SST and realizable k-ε results; maximum RH difference was 0.04 units. The validation team concluded that model fidelity is sufficient to support the COU decision at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/vr-03-solver-verification",
